---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SiteHeader from '../components/SiteHeader.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About Chronicles of Ethium — a novel for readers aged twelve and up."
>
  <SiteHeader slot="header" />

  <div class="container prose">
    <h1 class="page-title">About this book</h1>

    <p>
      <em>Chronicles of Ethium</em> is a novel retelling of a Dungeons &amp; Dragons
      campaign played around a table with dice, maps, and far too many bad jokes.
      After each session, the story is rewritten as prose you can read like any other
      book.
    </p>

    <p>
      It is written for readers aged twelve and up — clear enough for younger readers
      to follow alone, but with enough mystery and peril to keep older readers turning
      pages. Think classic adventure stories: brave companions, strange lands, and
      choices that matter.
    </p>

    <p>
      The black-and-white illustrations echo old fighting fantasy books — woodcut plates
      beside the text, as if you had pulled this volume from a dusty shelf in a very
      old library.
    </p>

    <p>
      New chapters appear after each game session. Start from the
      <a href="/chapters/">table of contents</a>, or jump straight in with
      <a href="/">Begin reading</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
